{
  "id": "class_0033",
  "name": "Candlewright of the Sunken Forge",
  "title_completion": "a Candlewright of the Sunken Forge",
  "flavor_text": "Where the dwarves once hammered hymns into hot iron, you carry their last ember \u2014 not in your hands, but somewhere behind your sternum, warm and inexhaustible. The brine has swallowed the halls, the coal seams have gone quiet, but the light remembers. You strike with the devotion of a priest who never knew the god, only the glow.",
